annotationA: Prolyl-tRNA synthetase, mitochondrial, isoform A; ATP binding; glycine-tRNA ligase activity; proline-tRNA ligase activity. It is involved in the biological process described with: prolyl-tRNA aminoacylation; glycyl-tRNA aminoacylation
annotationB: Alanine--tRNA ligase, cytoplasmic; Catalyzes the attachment of alanine to tRNA(Ala) in a two-step reaction: alanine is first activated by ATP to form Ala- AMP and then transferred to the acceptor end of tRNA(Ala). Also edits incorrectly charged tRNA(Ala) via its editing domain; Belongs to the class-II aminoacyl-tRNA synthetase family
